        <div class="pass-type-label">Active retrieval passes</div>
        <p>Cases with a <code>retrievalPrecision</code> assertion that was satisfied. The only pass type that demonstrates verified retrieval capability. A system cannot accumulate these by returning everything or nothing.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="pass-type-card">
        <div class="pass-type-label">Structural passes</div>
        <p>Cases asserting scope isolation, supersession exclusion, or type routing without a precision assertion, and the structural property holds.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="pass-type-card">
        <div class="pass-type-label">Trivially empty passes</div>
        <p>Cases where the expected result set is empty by design (empty query, <code>maxBeliefs: 0</code>). Any system returning an empty set passes by construction. <code>retrievalPrecision</code> is null for these cases.</p>
