            <td><span class="val-bad">0.94</span></td>
            <td><span class="val-bad">1.00</span></td>
            <td><span class="val-bad">0.92</span></td>
            <td><span class="val-bad">1.00</span></td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <p style="margin-top: 1.5rem; font-size: 0.875rem;">Hindsight at turn 10: drift score 1.0 with the correct belief absent entirely (recall 0). Not ranked low — missing from the result set, with 4 explicit noise belief violations flagged on top of a full-corpus return.</p>

    <!-- Session latency -->
    <h3 style="margin-top: 3rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">Session-turn latency</h3>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 1rem;">Single-turn latency is not session latency. Under session load, all three comparison systems degrade 3–4×. Hindsight, 672ms single-turn, exceeds 2,700ms mean per session turn.</p>

